<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="1060" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1060">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15567.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Confidential Agent of the Provisional
                                    Government of Mexico</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-22">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 22, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department acknowledges the receipt
                            of your letter of July 21, regarding the action of General Calles of the
                            Carranza forces in taking the town of Naco in violation of an agreement
                            entered into between General Calles and Governor Maytorena.</p>
                        <p>In view of the conditions surrounding the making of this agreement,
                            special attention is being given to the matter referred to by you in
                            your letter of July 21, as a result of communications from the War
                            Department.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>